e Township, Wall, Clifton, Pompton Lakes, Flanders, Glen Gardner, Fairview, Flemington, Neptune and on Staten Island.</p>','About Us','','inherit','open','open','','42-revision-v1','','','2014-06-26 15:23:23','2014-06-26 15:23:23','',42,'http://localhost:8888/?p=43',0,'revision','',0),(44,1,'2014-06-26 15:26:00','2014-06-26 15:26:00','<h2>A Timeline of Foley\'s History:</h2> \r\n\r\n<p><strong>1957</strong>- Foley Machinery begins business as a Caterpillar Dealer</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>1967</strong>- Foley Machinery moves HQ from Union, NJ to Piscataway, NJ</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>1967</strong>- Bermuda added to territory</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>1969</strong>- Purchased Lift Truck Business</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>1971</strong>- 1st Parts Drop is established (Dick\'s Gas Station in Paramus)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>1971</strong>- Ed Foley, Jr. founds the NJ Alliance for Action</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>1978</strong>- Kim Foley becomes President</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>1980</strong>- Power Systems is launched</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>1984</strong>- Ed Foley retires; Kim becomes CEO and Chairman of the Board</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>1988</strong>- Monroe Branch is opened</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>1990</strong>- Foley Machinery is renamed Foley, Incorporated</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>1996</strong>- Foley Rents is launched</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>1999</strong>- Jamie and Ryan Foley join the company</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>1998</strong>- Foley Truck Division building is opened</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>2005</strong>- Jamie Foley is named President</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>2007</strong>- Foley, Incorporated celebrates 50th Anniversary</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>2007</strong>- Ryan Foley named Vice President of Foley Rents</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>2009</strong>- Jamie Foley elected CEO of Foley, Inc.</p>\r\n','History','','publish','open','open','','history','','','2014-06-26 15:47:42','2014-06-26 15:47:42','',82,'http://localhost:8888/?page_id=44',0,'page','',0),(45,1,'2014-06-26 15:26:00','2014-06-26 15:26:00','<h2>A Ti