ligible full time employees both Union and Non-Union, are offered several competitive benefit programs that are affordable, flexible and comprehensive to meet their individual and family needs. Programs include medical, dental, prescription, retirement and several tax-savings programs to name a few.\r\n\r\nThis list only describes the highlights of the Foley, Incorporated benefit program. This list does not constitute a contract or obligation by Foley, Incorporated to maintain any particular benefit program. Benefits are reviewed and updated periodically, with changes at the sole discretion of the company.\r\n<h2 style=\"color: #000000;\">Healthcare Benefits</h2>\r\nFoley, Incorporated provides medical, dental and prescription drug plans including coverage for preventative services. Each plan provides in and out of network benefits.\r\n<h2 style=\"color: #000000;\">Dental Benefits</h2>\r\nOur Dental Plan provides the option of selecting coverage with or without medical coverage.\r\n<h2 style=\"color: #000000;\">Supplemental Insurance Plans</h2>\r\nPersonal insurance is available through employer sponsored AFLAC policies. Policies offered are Cancer protection, Accident Insurance and Short Term Disability.\r\n<h2 style=\"color: #000000;\">Flexible Spending Accounts</h2>\r\nFlexible Spending Accounts (FSA) are available to help pay for Healthcare and Dependent Care on a pre-tax basis.\r\n<h2 style=\"color: #000000;\">Life Insurance</h2>\r\nLife Insurance Coverage is provided to eligible employees; at no cost.\r\n<h2 style=\"color: #000000;\">401K Plan</h2>\r\nFoley, Incorporated is committed to your success at work and to helping eligible employees succeed in retirement. Our 401K Plan offers 100% \"matching\" contributions, up to the first 5%, of your pre-tax contribution through MassMutual Financial Group.\r\n<h2 style=\"color: #000000;\">Retirement Program</h2>\r\nPension and Annuity plan for Union employees.\r\n<h2 style=\"color: #000000;\">Tuition Reimbursement</h2>\r\nFull time employees who have completed six months of service are reimbursed, on a set fee schedule, for successful completion of job related continued higher education courses.\r\n<h2 style=\"color: #000000;\">Vacation &amp; Personal Days</h2>\r\nEligible full time employees will receive company paid vacation time based on seniority. In addition, employees can earn up to 5 personal days per year.\r\n<h2 style=\"color: #000000;\">Holidays</h2>\r\nPaid holidays to eligible employees; New Year\'s Day, Presidents Day, Good Friday, Memorial Day, July 4th, Labor Day, Thanksgiving and day after, Christmas Eve Day, Christmas Day and New Year\'s Eve Day.\r\n<h2 style=\"color: #000000;\">Other Special Benefits</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Employee Recognition Program</li>\r\n	<li>\"Values\" based Leadership</li>\r\n	<li>Annual Performance Reviews</li>\r\n	<li>Smoke Free Campus</li>\r\n	<li>Advancement opportunities</li>\r\n	<li>Military Leave</li>\r\n	<li>Family Leave</li>\r\n	<li>Direct Deposit</li>\r\n	<li>Credit Union (CEFCU)</li>\r\n	<li>Employee Assistance Program (EAP)</li>\r\n	<li>Training Programs</li>\r\n	<li>Job Referral Program</li>\r\n	<li>Company provided Field Service Vehicles (Technicians)</li>\r\n	<li>Tool purchase plans (Technicians)</li>\r\n	<li>Company provided Uniforms (Parts/Service employees)</li>\r\n	<li>Safety shoes allowance (Parts/Service employees)</li>\r\n	<li>Prescription safety glasses allowance (Parts/Service employees)</li>\r\n</ul>','Employee Benefits','','publish','open','open','','employee-benefits','','','2014-06-27 14:57:48','2014-06-27 14:57:48','',62,'http://localhost:8888/?page_id=64',0,'page','',0),(65,1,'2014-06-26 15:44:37','2014-06-26 15:44:37','','Employee Benefits','','inherit','open','open','','64-revision-v1','','','2014-06-26 15:44:37','2014-06-26 15:44:37','',64,'http://localhost:8888/?p=65',0,'revision','',0),(66,1,'2014-06-26 15:44:56','2014-06-26 15:44:56','','Emergency Preparedness','','publish','open','open','','emergency-p