\n        <tr>\r\n        	<td>Rear PTO Capacity (rotation opposite of engine, at 1.25 engine speed)</td>\r\n            <td>1000.0 ft-lb 1356.0 NÂ·m</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n        	<td>Side PTO Capacity (rotation same as engine, ration determined by PTO adaptor)</td>\r\n            <td>700.0 ft-lb</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h2>Benefits and Features</h2>\r\n\r\n<h3>HEAVY-HAULING CAPACITY</h3>\r\n<p>The CT681â€™s set-forward axle, rugged design and industrial styling make it ideal for hauling heavy loads or working in extreme conditions. Aluminum alloy cab construction reduces overall weight for maximum payloads.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>ATTACHMENT-READY DESIGN</h3>\r\n<p>Our integral Front Frame Extension (FFE) option makes it easy to mount attachments like snow plows, hose reels, winches and hydraulic pumps. Mixer installation is simple thanks to vertical tie-in plates mounted behind the cab.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>SHIFT-LONG PRODUCTIVITY</h3>\r\n<p>Comfortable drivers are safe, productive drivers. The CT681â€™s wide, spacious cab is filled with ergonomic details to reduce fatigue and thoughtful features to enhance driver comfort, all shift long.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>SAFER DRIVING</h3>\r\n<p>Our ergonomically designed dashboard and center stack layout give drivers complete command and control. All controls, levers, switches and gauges are positioned to maximize safety and minimize fatigue, so drivers can stay focused on the job at hand.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>SMOOTH, QUIET RIDE</h3>\r\n<p>Our tuned cab air suspension system, premium grade sound insulation kit, and durable routing and clipping wire system dramatically reduce vibration and cab noise.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>VOCATIONAL-SPECIFIC POWER</h3>\r\n<p>Under the hood, the CT681 is powered by a Cat CT Series Vocational Truck Engine with ratings specific to vocational truck applications and a horsepower/torque combination to tackle the toughest jobs.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>AUTOMATIC SHIFTING</h3>\r\n<p>Performance-matched with your engine to deliver rugged durability, smooth shifting and optimum power, the Cat CX31 Automatic Transmission will help you maximize your CT681â€™s uptime, fuel economy and productivity. (Other transmission options are available.)</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>UNMATCHED SUPPORT</h3>\r\n<p>Your CT681 comes with the best on-the-ground support team in the business. Your Cat dealer not only offers bumper-to-bumper service, but also can help you order the exact truck you need with expertise on custom options ranging from transmissions to suspensions and axles.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Equipment</h2>\r\n<h3>CT681 STANDARD EQUIPMENT</h3>\r\n<strong>Chasis</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Set-forward axle, 114-inch bumper to back of cab (BBC)</li>\r\n\r\n	<li>12.25-inch rail size: 120,000 psi yield strength</li>\r\n\r\n	<li>Above-rail radiator</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<strong>Axles</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Meritor & Dana options</li>\r\n\r\n	<li>6x4 truck configuration</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<strong>Front Suspension</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Parabolic taper leaf for a smoother ride</li>\r\n	<li>Shock absorbers standard</li>\r\n	<li>Optional two-stage, multi-leaf, shackle-type with shocks</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<strong>Rear Suspension</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Hendrickson offerings: HMX, RT/RTE, RS, R & PriMaax</li>\r\n	<li>Chalmers standard & high articulation</li>\r\n	<li>Capacities from 40,000-85,000 lbs.</li>\r\n\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n\r\n<strong>Fuel Tank</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>80-, 100- & 120-gallon capacities</li>\r\n	<li>Single left or dual under cab/back of cab options</li>\r\n	<li>Aluminum alloy construction</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>CT681 OPTIONAL EQUIPMENT</h3>\r\n<strong>Chassis</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Integral Front Frame Extension (FFE)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<strong>Transmission</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Cat CX31 Automatic Transmission</li>\r\n	<li>A variety of manual transmissions and the UltrashiftÂ® Plus Vocational Transmission built by Eaton</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r