e\'ve got you covered.</p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\">Total Solutions Service Shop- we repair and maintain all of the essential components in your vehicle:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n<div><strong>Transmission Repair or Replacement</strong></div></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n<div><strong>Driveline (U-joints, Carrier Brg, Driveshaft Replacement)</strong></div></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n<div><strong>Major Engine Work (Overhauls, Cylinder Head)</strong></div></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n<div><strong>PM Services</strong></div></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n<div><strong>Cooling System</strong></div></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n<div><strong>Brakes</strong></div></li>\r\n	<li>\r\n<div><strong>And more!</strong></div></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2 style=\"color: #000000;\">Contact Information</h2>\r\n833 Centennial Ave.\r\nPiscataway, NJ 08855\r\nService: 732-885-8152\r\nParts: 732-885-8257','On Highway','','inherit','open','open','','217-revision-v1','','','2014-06-27 17:31:23','2014-06-27 17:31:23','',217,'http://localhost:8888/?p=372',0,'revision','',0),(373,1,'2014-06-27 17:33:50','2014-06-27 17:33:50','<h2 style=\"color: #000000;\">On Highway Emissions Solutions</h2>\r\nCaterpillar has the right environmental solutions for your on-highway vehicles. Backed by the reliability and performance of Peterson Power Systems, these solutions reduce emissions and are tailored to fit a wide range of diesel engines.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Oxidation Catalysts</strong>Â create a chemical reaction with exhaust gases as they pass over the catalyst material. This reaction reduces some of the particulate matter and converts a large portion of carbon monoxide, hydrocarbons and other emissions into carbon dioxide and water.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Diesel Particulate Filters</strong>Â use special filters to reduce particulate matter (PM), carbon monoxide and hydrocarbon emissions. Exhaust backpressure is maintained through passive regeneration, a process that automatically removes particulate buildup.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nCAT Diesel Particulate Filter solutions include diagnostic module for backpressure, exhaust temperature monitoring and datalogging.\r\n\r\nThe type of solution appropriate for a specific application depends on the configuration of the vehicle\'s exhaust system and the specific emissions targeted by applicable emissions regulations.\r\n\r\nFor more information regarding emissions reduction technology, please contact:\r\n\r\n<a style=\"color: #336699;\" href=\"mailto:jgoleskie@foleyinc.com\">John GoleskieÂ </a>','Emissions Solutions ','','inherit','open','open','','137-revision-v1','','','2014-06-27 17:33:50','2014-06-27 17:33:50','',137,'http://localhost:8888/?p=373',0,'revision','',0),(374,1,'2014-06-27 17:34:56','2014-06-27 17:34:56','<h2 style=\"color: #000000;\">Foley is an Authorized NJ DEP BART Installer</h2>\r\n<strong>Foley, Inc.</strong>Â is an authorized NJ DEP Best Available Retrofit Technology (BART) Installer. We have performed retrofit installations on 1,800 on-highway vehicles under the NJ DEP retrofit program.\r\n\r\nBy selectingÂ <strong>Foley, Inc.</strong>as your retrofit installer, your compliance workload will be easy and trouble free. Listed below are the support services and installation conveniences that we provide.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a style=\"color: #336699;\" href=\"http://www.myfoleyinc.com/files/Best_Available_Retrofit_Installer.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Best Retrofit Installer Brochure</a></li>\r\n	<li><a style=\"color: #336699;\" href=\"http://www.myfoleyinc.com/files/Best_Available_Retrofit_Installer_Letter.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Best Retrofit Installer Letter</a></li>\r\n	<li><a style=\"color: #336699;\" href=\"http://www.myfoleyinc.com/files/DEP_Diesel_Risk_Reduction_Program_Letter.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">DEP Diesel Risk Reduction Program Letter</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>\r\nFoley Inc.</strong>Â will provide your fleet with:\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>A review of all NJ DEP regulations for Private Commercial Buses.</li>\r\n	<li>Management of all required NJ DEP documentation.</li>\r\n	<li>A complete fleet assessment and exhaust temperature data logging on your buses at your location(s).</li>\r\n	<li>We will submit your fleet profile to NJDEP for approval at your location(s).</li>\r\n	<li>We will perform the retrofit installations for all chassis and engine manufacturers (Cat/DDC/Cummins) at your location(s), days or evenings.</li>\r\n	<li>State of the art products from Cat and Donaldson.</li>\r\n	<li>Retrofit installation maintenance training and driver training at your location(s).</li>\r\n</ol>','School Bus Solutions','','inherit','open','open','','181-revision-v1','','','2014-06-27 17:34:56','2014-06-27 17:34:56','',181,'http://localhost:8888/?p=374',0,'revision','',0),(375,1,'2014-06-27 17:36:11','2014-06-27 17:36:11','','School Bus Solutions','','inherit','open','open','','181-revision-v1','','','2014-06-27 17:36:11','2014-06-27 17:36:11','',181,'http://localhost:8888/?p=375',0,'revision','',0),(376,1,'2014-06-27 17:36:40','2014-06-27 17:36:40','<h2 style=\"color: #000000;\">Foley is an Authorized NJ DEP BART Installer</h2>\r\n<strong>Foley, Inc.</strong>Â is an authorized NJ DEP Best Available Retrofit Technology (BART) Installer. We have performed retrofit installations on 1,800 on-highway vehicles under the NJ DEP retrofit program.\r\n\r\nBy selectingÂ <strong>Foley, Inc.</strong>as your retrofit installer, your compliance workload will be easy and trouble free. Listed below are the support services and installation conveniences that we provide.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a style=\"color: #336699;\" href=\"http://www.myfoleyinc.com/files/Best_Available_Retrofit_Installer.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Best Retrofit Installer Brochure</a></li>\r\n	<li><a style=\"color: #336699;\" href=\"http://www.myfoleyinc.com/files/Best_Available_Retrofit_Installer_Letter.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Best Retrofit Installer Letter</a></li>\r\n	<li><a style=\"color: #336699;\" href=\"http://www.myfoleyinc.com/files/DEP_Diesel_Risk_Reduction_Program_Letter.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">DEP Diesel Risk Reduction Program Letter</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>\r\nFoley Inc.</strong>Â will provide your fleet with:\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>A review of all NJ DEP regulations for Private Commercial Buses.</li>\r\n	<li>Management of all required NJ DEP documentation.</li>\r\n	<li>A complete fleet assessment and exhaust temperature data logging on your buses at your location(s).</li>\r\n	<li>We will submit your fleet profile to NJDEP for approval at your location(s).</li>\r\n	<li>We will perform the retrofit installations for all chassis and engine manufacturers (Cat/DDC/Cummins) at your location(s), days or evenings.</li>\r\n	<li>State of the art products from Cat and Donaldson.</li>\r\n	<li>Retrofit installation maintenance training and driver training at your location(s).</li>\r\n</ol>','Coach Retrofit','','inherit','open','open','','179-revision-v1','','','2014-06-27 17:36:40','2014-06-27 17:36:40','',179,'http://localhost:8888/?p=376',0,'revision','',0),(377,1,'2014-06-27 17:37:38','2014-06-27 17:37:38','<h2 style=\"color: #000000;\">One Safe Solution</h2>\r\nFoley Inc. has a One Safe Solution for all types of school buses, regardless of engine or bus manufacture to retrofit a Closed Crankcase Ventilation System, Diesel Oxidation Catalysts, or Diesel Particulate Filters. Foley can install these devices to minimize the downtime of each bus so you can comply with the state requirements.\r\n\r\n<strong>Closed Crankcase Ventilation Systems (CCVS)</strong>\r\nThe State of NJ will require all school buses by 2009 to be retrofitted with Closed Crankcase Ventilation Systems and the State of NJ will subsidize the cost of parts and installation of the CCVS on all school buses. This technology will improve the air quality inside the school bus by reducing the exposure of children to the harmful affects of diesel particulate matter emissions.\r\n\r\n<strong>Diesel Oxidation Catalysts (DOC)</strong>\r\nDiesel Oxidation Catalysts help school bus owners lower emissions on all buses equipped with any brand of diesel engine. This technology replaces the standard muffler and removes some particulate matter, carbon monoxide, and hydrocarbons from exhaust gas.\r\n\r\n<strong>Diesel Particulate Filters (DPF)</strong>\r\nDiesel Particulate Filters are a more effective in reducing particulate matter emissions. They typically remove 90 percent of fine particulate matter from engine exhaust gas and significantly reduce hydrocarbons and carbon monoxide.\r\n\r\nFor more information regarding emissions reduction technology, please contactÂ <a style=\"color: #336699;\" href=\"http://www.foleyinc.com/on_highway/on_highway_emissions_solutions/directory/aaron_israel\">Aaron Israel, Emissions Specialist</a>.','School Bus Solutions','','inherit','open','open','','181-revision-v1','','','2014-06-27 17:37:38','2014-06-27 17:37:38','',181,'http://localhost:8888/?p=377',0,'revision','',0),(378,1,'2014-06-27 17:40:12','2014-06-27 17:40:12','<div class=\"text-column\">\r\n<h2 style=\"color: #000000;\">Lower Truck Emissions</h2>\r\nEmission reduction technology is also available for refuse truck and bus applications. Diesel Oxidation Catalysts (DOC) and Diesel Particulate Filters (DPF) lower emissions on any refuse truck or bus equipped with Caterpillar and other brands of diesel engines. These technologies replace the standard muffler and removes particulate matter, carbon monoxide, and unburned hydrocarbons from exhaust gas.\r\n\r\nFor more information regarding emissions reduction technology, please contactÂ <a style=\"color: #336699;\" href=\"http://www.foleyinc.com/on_highway/on_highway_emissions_solutions/directory/aaron_israel\">Aaron Israel, Emissions Specialist</a>.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"photo-column\">\r\n\r\n<strong>Downloads:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a style=\"color: #336699;\" href=\"http://www.foleyinc.com/assets/uploads/NJ%20DEP%20Refuse%20Truck%20Letter.pdf\">NJ DEP Refuse Truck Letter</a></li>\r\n	<li><a style=\"color: #336699;\" href=\"http://www.foleyinc.com/assets/uploads/Refuse%20Truck%20Customer%20Letter.pdf\">Refuse Truck Customer Letter</a></li>\r\n	<li><a style=\"color: #336699;\" href=\"http://www.foleyinc.com/assets/uploads/On%20Highway%20Emissions%20Solutions.pdf\">On Highway Emissions Solutions</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>','Refuse Truck Solutions','','inherit','open','open','','183-revision-v1','','','2014-06-27 17:40:12','2014-06-27 17:40:12','',183,'http://localhost:8888/?p=378',0,'revision','',0),(379,1,'2014-06-27 19:32:13','2014-06-27 19:32:13','','slide01','','inherit','open','open','','slide01-2','','','2014-06-27 19:32:13','2014-06-27 19:32:13','',27,'http://localhost:8888/content/uploads/2014/06/slide011.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(380,1,'2014-06-27 19:32:16','2014-06-27 19:32:16','','slide02','','inherit','open','open','','slide02-2','','','2014-06-27 19:32:16','2014-06-27 19:32:16','',27,'http://localhost:8888/content/uploads/2014/06/slide021.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(381,1,'2014-06-27 19:32:19','2014-06-27 19:32:19','','slide03','','inherit','open','open','','slide03-2','','','2014-06-27 19:32:19','2014-06-27 19:32:19','',27,'http://localhost:8888/content/uploads/2014/06/slide031.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(382,1,'2014-06-27 19:32:22','2014-06-27 19:32:22','','slide04','','inherit','open','open','','slide04-2','','','2014-06-27 19:32:22','2014-06-27 19:32:22','',27,'http://localhost:8888/content/uploads/2014/06/slide041.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(383,1,'2014-06-27 19:32:24','2014-06-27 19:32:24','','slide05','','inherit','open','open','','slide05-2','','','2014-06-27 19:32:24','2014-06-27 19:32:24','',27,'http://localhost:8888/content/uploads/2014/06/slide051.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0);
